ognostic significance as assessed by magnetic resonance imaging. <em>Eur Heart J</em> 2005;26(6):549–557.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/eurheartj/ehi147">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15713695/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Sequelae+of+acute+myocardial+infarction+regarding+cardiac+structure+and+function+and+their+prognostic+significance+as+assessed+by+magnetic+resonance+imaging&amp;author=V+Hombach&amp;author=O+Grebe&amp;author=N+Merkle&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Eur+Heart+J&amp;pages=549-557&amp;doi=10.1093%2Feurheartj%2Fehi147&amp;pmid=15713695">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">34.</div><div id="r34" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Bodi V, Sanchis J, Nunez J, et al. Prognostic value of a comprehensive cardiac magnetic resonance assessment soon after a first ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction. <em>JACC Cardiovasc Imaging</em> 2009;2(7):835–842.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jcmg.2009.03.011">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19608133/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Prognostic+value+of+a+comprehensive+cardiac+magnetic+resonance+assessment+soon+after+a+first+ST-segment+elevation+myocardial+infarction&amp;author=V+Bodi&amp;author=J+Sanchis&amp;author=J+Nunez&amp;publication_year=2009&amp;journal=JACC+Cardiovasc+Imaging&amp;pages=835-842&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jcmg.2009.03.011&amp;pmid=19608133">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">35.</div><div id="r35" class="cita